Class GenericInputMethodControl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.situx.postagger.main.gui.ime.jquery.GenericInputMethodControl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericInputMethod.Control
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AkkInputTermSource.AkkadMethodControl, TreeBuilder.AkkadianMethodControl

    public class GenericInputMethodControl
extends java.lang.Object
implements GenericInputMethod.Control
    An base implementation of TermInputMethod.Control that supports the base control options: raw window usage (raw below the spot or inline) chooser orientation (vertical or horizontal)

      • isUsingRawWindow

        public boolean isUsingRawWindow()
        Description copied from interface: GenericInputMethod.Control
        Obtain whether the method should use a window below-the-spot for raw input (this window is separate from the Java Input Method Framework's below-the-spot handling of converted characters). If false, raw input will be composed inline with converted but uncommitted text.
        Specified by:
        isUsingRawWindow in interface GenericInputMethod.Control
        Returns:
        true if using a raw window
